Defendant James E Koch in court with attorney Mark Emil Kershek.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 and 4.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2 and 3 are dismissed by operation of law.  Counts #5 and 6 are dismissed and read in. 
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

4 YEARS 2 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT; (CREDIT 0 DAYS);
  -  1 YEAR 2 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
  -  3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

DL REVOCATION: 36 MONTHS;
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 MONTHS;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Attend Victim Impact Panel (completed 6/17/15).
*Not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed. 

FINE: $1519.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail);

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (apply cash bail - to be forwarded to Town of Brookfield Police Department);

Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Count #4:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

3 YEARS 2 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT; (CREDIT 0 DAYS); (concurrent to Count #1);
  -  1 YEAR 2 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

COSTS: $268.00 (apply cash bail);
DNA SURCHARGE: $250.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be refunded to poster);

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
See Count #1.
